-- Artisan Named U.S. Stock Fund Manager of Year
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2012-01-04T19:55:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/artisan-named-u-s-stock-fund-manager-of-year.html
A team that manages three mutual
funds for Milwaukee-based Artisan Partners LP was named 2011
domestic stock manager of the year by  Morningstar Inc. (MORN)   Scott Satterwhite, James Kieffer and George Sertl, who
together run three value-style funds, won the award, the
Chicago-based company said today in a statement on its website.
The teamâ€™s $7.2 billion Artisan Mid Cap Value, the $2.8 billion
Artisan Small Cap Value and the $562 million Artisan Value
outperformed 99 percent, 65 percent and 96 percent of peers over
the past year, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The team that manages the $4.3 billion Tweedy, Browne
Global Value Fund won the award for best international stock
fund manager. The fund, which topped 95 percent of rivals, is
run by William Browne, John Spears, Tom Shrager and Bob Wyckoff.  John Carlson, who oversees the $4.2 billion  Fidelity New
Markets Income Fund (FNMIX) , was named fixed-income fund manager of the
year. He outperformed 99 percent of competitors over the last
year, Bloomberg data show.  The awards are based on short- and long-term performance
adjusted for risk, according to Morningstar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
